Class ReexportedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.events.ReexportedEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ReexportedEvent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The class ReexportedEvent implements the description of events that are exported by submodels and re-exported by an ancestor coupled model.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2018-05-02

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

      • ReexportedEvent

        public ReexportedEvent(java.lang.String exportingModelURI,
                       java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sourceEventType,
                       java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sinkEventType,
                       EventConverterI converter)
        create a description of a re-exported type of events where the type of events coming from the source requires a conversion to the one going to the sink.

        Contract

         pre     exportingModelURI != null
 pre     sourceEventType != null && sinkEventType != null
 pre     converter.getDomain().isAssignableFrom(sourceEventType)
 pre     sinkEventType.isAssignableFrom(converter.getCodomain())
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Parameters:
        exportingModelURI - URI of the model exporting the events.
        sourceEventType - type of events coming from the source.
        sinkEventType - type of events going to the sink.
        converter - conversion function.
